    <body>
      <head>Herr and Frau Levy</head>
      <div>

        <p>Travellers from <ref cRef="entity-002501">Berlin</ref> to <ref cRef="entity-008467"
            >Santiago</ref>, <ref cRef="entity-005845">Chile</ref> in the summer of 1936, whom <ref
            cRef="entity-000771">Jeanette Schenker</ref> encountered.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p><ref cRef="entity-000771">Jeanette Schenker</ref>, during her trip to South America in
          April–September 1936, met Herr and Frau Levy, who were travelling from <ref
            cRef="entity-002501">Berlin</ref> with their nephew, on board the transatlantic ship the
            <hi rend="italic">Orazio</hi> on May 12. <ref cRef="entity-000771">Jeanette</ref> went
          ashore with them when the ship put in at Cristóbal, and on June 3 disembarked with them at
            <ref cRef="entity-008467">Santiago</ref>. <ref cRef="entity-000771">Jeanette</ref>
          described Herr Levy as “a typical disgusting Berlin Jew.” She later encountered the nephew
          again in <ref cRef="entity-008467">Santiago</ref>.</p>
      </div>

